Details

This object is a named list containing 3 elements:

  • genotypes (data.frame): Genotypic data encoded in allele doses of 100 fictitious individuals with 3333 SNP markers. These individuals have 10 chromosomes of length 10^6 bases pairs.

  • snpCoord (data.frame): Coordinates of the 3333 individuals' markers. This data.frame contains 3 columns: chr, pos and SNPid.

  • snpEffects (numeric): "true" effects of the 3333 individuals' markers about a fictitious quantitative trait based on an additive architecture.
